# Orchestrator — Startup Brief & Plan of Attack

## Run identity

- **slug:** `construction-company-website`
- **run dir:** `upwork-runs/construction-company-website/`
- **demo target:** `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/construction-company-website/`
- **live demo URL (post-deploy):** `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/construction-company-website/`
- **work-sample route:** `/work-samples/construction-company-website`
- **feature richness:** 10 / 10 — build a genuinely full-featured, production-quality marketing site with several real working features and extra-clean polish ("medium rare" — the client wants the UI to look *exceptional* on a conceptually simple site).

## What the client actually asked for (raw posting digest)

A professional website for a construction company. The owner builds homes, does
excavation, and does residential + commercial construction. U.S.-only freelancer
requirement (Michael qualifies). Price negotiable. Explicit must-haves:

1. **Landing page with a full video background** (hero). This is called out twice — it is the signature feature, treat it as the hero.
2. **Services page with pricing.**
3. **Contact page.**
4. **Projects page** (portfolio / gallery of past work).
5. **Strong "construction market" theme and styling** — must read as a real, established construction firm.
6. **Extra-clean, very professional UX/UI.** The client emphasized polish over feature sprawl: simple app, exceptionally executed. "Medium rare" = refined, confident, not overcooked/gimmicky, not raw/unfinished.

## Plan of attack (downstream pipeline)

Recommended step order (use a layout with deploy + CEO if available):

`intake -> planner -> ceo -> researcher -> demo-builder -> ceo -> deploy -> deploy-test -> media-capture -> proposal-writer -> evaluator`

### intake
- Produce `brief.json`. Capture every explicit requirement above as a discrete,
  gradable line item: (1) video-background landing, (2) services + pricing page,
  (3) contact page, (4) projects page, (5) construction theme/styling, (6) extra-clean professional UI.
- Note constraints: U.S.-only (no action needed, just record), price negotiable,
  feature richness 10.

### planner
- Confirm **full build** (not prototype) — richness 10, no backend blocker, scope
  fits the caps. Hero = video-background landing + services/pricing. Supporting =
  projects gallery + working contact form.
- **Bespoke design direction (do NOT use michaelwegter.com's look).** Construction
  industry = trust, weight, craftsmanship. Suggested direction for planner to
  refine: a grounded, masculine-but-premium palette (deep charcoal/graphite, warm
  concrete grays, a single confident accent — safety-amber/hi-vis yellow OR a
  steel/blueprint blue), strong industrial typography (e.g. a condensed/grotesk
  display face like Archivo/Anton/Oswald paired with a clean humanist sans like
  Inter/Source Sans for body), generous whitespace, big confident imagery, subtle
  motion. Aim for "established regional builder with a great agency site," not a
  template. Define exact hex + real Google Font families.
- Hero video: plan a tasteful construction-site loop (drone over a site, framing a
  home, machinery) with a dark gradient overlay so headline text stays legible.
  Source a royalty-free clip (Pexels/Coverr/Mixkit) OR a CSS/canvas fallback if no
  clip is safely available — record the choice. Must autoplay muted, loop,
  playsinline, with a poster image and a reduced-motion fallback.
- Write the requirement-to-feature traceability matrix.

### researcher
- Gather real construction-firm site conventions + 2-3 competitor/agency examples
  for visual reference. Find royalty-free hero video + project imagery sources
  (license-clear). Confirm the existing scaffold to clone: AppFrame is reused as-is
  for the route; the demo itself is a self-contained `index.html` + `assets/`
  (default form). Pull font + clip URLs so demo-builder doesn't have to hunt.

### demo-builder
- Build into `public/demos/construction-company-website/`. Self-contained static
  app (vanilla or React-via-CDN) is the right call here — it's a marketing site.
- Pages/sections: **Home (video hero)**, **Services + Pricing**, **Projects**,
  **Contact**. Multi-page feel via routing or anchored sections — make it feel like
  a real multi-page site with a sticky header nav + footer.
- Real working features to hit richness 10: video-background hero with overlay +
  CTA, services grid with transparent pricing cards/tiers, filterable projects
  gallery with lightbox, a **functional contact form** (validate + success state;
  wire to a tiny mw-backend blueprint OR a client-side mailto/stub with a
  convincing success UX — planner decides; if backend, seed nothing sensitive),
  testimonials/stats counters, "get a quote" flow, responsive + mobile nav,
  accessibility pass, reduced-motion support. Register in `workSamples.js`
  (next sequential id; category "Creative" or "Productivity"; frameStyle to match).
- Hard gates: builds + loads with no console errors on first paint; demo link must
  later appear in cover letter AND deck; no em/en dashes anywhere.

### deploy -> deploy-test
- Push michaelwegter.com (and mw-backend only if a contact blueprint was added).
  Verify live URLs (site 200, /work-samples route 200, /health ok if backend).
- Playwright the live site: video hero loads, nav works across all four
  pages/sections, contact form submits + shows success, projects lightbox opens,
  responsive. Emit VERDICT. Fail loops back to demo-builder.

### media-capture -> proposal-writer -> evaluator
- Capture hero (video frame), services/pricing, projects gallery, contact.
- Cover letter + one-pager + PPTX deck in Michael's voice, styled to the demo's
  construction design language (NOT the portfolio look). Address all 6
  requirements explicitly, reference the live demo by name + link in both letter
  and deck. No em/en dashes.
- Evaluator enforces the 6 hard gates; bounded reflection loop on any miss.

## Quality bar / guardrails for this run

- This is a **design-led** run. The client's bar is polish, not feature count, so
  the win condition is: it looks like a premium, trustworthy construction firm and
  the four pages all genuinely work. Don't ship anything that feels like a free
  template.
- The **video background is the make-or-break detail** — it must be smooth,
  legible (text overlay readable), performant, and have a graceful fallback. Test
  it on the live deploy specifically.
- Respect token-budget rules: intermediates to disk, narrow reads, clone the
  AppFrame pattern, demo touches <= ~12 files, build timeout 3 min.
- Bespoke palette/type only; never michaelwegter.com's dark gallery theme inside
  the demo.

## Status

Setup complete. Run directory ready at
`upwork-runs/construction-company-website/`. Next step: `intake`.
